just to use the bathroom.

00:36:30.524 --> 00:36:32.902
Next time, if you want to skip, invite me too.

00:36:33.025 --> 00:36:33.935
I’m lonely.

00:36:35.126 --> 00:36:35.826
Here.

00:36:37.901 --> 00:36:40.607
Yeah, we just got carried away talking.

00:36:42.168 --> 00:36:43.512
Where’s Jinn?

00:36:44.210 --> 00:36:44.922
He left.

00:36:45.415 --> 00:36:46.666
What? What about me?

00:36:46.666 --> 00:36:47.412
He said you were not leaving together.

00:36:47.412 --> 00:36:48.998
My ass!

00:36:48.998 --> 00:36:50.453
He just walked off. If you—

00:36:54.284 --> 00:36:54.979
Great.

00:37:01.634 --> 00:37:02.901
Let’s grab something to eat

00:37:03.866 --> 00:37:05.625
so you’ll stop complaining.

00:37:06.284 --> 00:37:08.364
Fine. Whatever.

00:37:09.062 --> 00:37:10.351
Anyone can just leave me behind.

00:37:11.891 --> 00:37:13.090
Except you.

00:37:16.007 --> 00:37:17.093
You, shut up.

00:37:17.504 --> 00:37:19.095
And walk.

00:37:23.059 --> 00:37:24.565
Jinn, open the door now.

00:37:24.804 --> 00:37:25.918
Jinn, open the door.

00:37:30.745 --> 00:37:32.079
Isn’t your hand already healed?

00:37:32.675 --> 00:37:34.903
There’s no reason for me
to be your chauffeur.

00:37:35.170 --> 00:37:35.782
Jinn.

00:37:38.452 --> 00:37:39.529
Bye-bye.

00:37:46.582 --> 00:37:47.456
Don’t.

00:37:48.113 --> 00:37:49.048
Go to work already.

00:37:50.958 --> 00:37:52.145
Fine, I’m going.

00:37:52.484 --> 00:37:53.183
Bye-bye.

00:37:59.655 --> 00:38:00.461
J!

00:38:00.749 --> 00:38:01.426
I’m off now.

00:38:29.172 --> 00:38:30.928
AUNTIE JENNY

00:38:34.051 --> 00:38:35.054
Hello, Auntie Jen.

00:38:35.958 --> 00:38:38.654
I got home and found
that J and his car were gone.

00:38:38.818 --> 00:38:40.437
And I can’t reach him.

00:38:40.910 --> 00:38:42.364
(Is he with you, Jinn?)

00:38:43.494 --> 00:38:44.451
He’s not.

00:38:49.866 --> 00:38:50.585
Damn it, J.

00:38:50.585 --> 00:38:51.357
What the hell are you playing now?

00:38:55.235 --> 00:38:56.099
TAR

00:38:56.633 --> 00:38:57.462
Hello, Tar.

00:38:59.023 --> 00:39:00.098
Yes. Sure.

00:39:03.918 --> 00:39:07.099
When was the first time
you saw those visions?

00:39:07.900 --> 00:39:10.676
I’d been seeing them vaguely
in my dreams for a while.

00:39:12.284 --> 00:39:14.262
But I saw them clearly for the first time…

00:39:15.536 --> 00:39:17.259
when I crashed the car.

00:39:18.656 --> 00:39:22.046
Are you saying you lost control
of the car because of this?

00:39:23.648 --> 00:39:24.788
I can’t explain it.

00:39:26.534 --> 00:39:31.671
It felt like I was pulled into it,
and I forgot I was even driving.

00:39:32.308 --> 00:39:33.636
The next thing I knew,

00:39:34.499 --> 00:39:36.008
the car had already crashed.

00:39:38.863 --> 00:39:42.134
But you usually only see
these visions when you’re asleep.

00:39:43.284 --> 00:39:45.776
So, at the circuit…

00:39:47.070 --> 00:39:51.002
That was the first time you saw
something while you were awake.

00:39:54.284 --> 00:39:55.730
I’ve never thought about that.

00:40:05.561 --> 00:40:08.140
You say you hate him the most,
yet you’re the first to come, Jinn.

00:40:10.400 --> 00:40:11.800
How could you let him drive?

00:40:12.848 --> 00:40:14.374
His hand isn’t even fully healed.

00:40:14.949 --> 00:40:17.109
My guy called, saying
someone trespassed on my circuit.

00:40:17.109 --> 00:40:19.115
When I got here,
he was already losing it like this.

00:40:22.287 --> 00:40:23.144
Where are you going, Jinn?

00:40:24.417 --> 00:40:25.393
To stop him.

00:40:59.168 --> 00:40:59.880
J!

00:41:00.702 --> 00:41:01.572
Asshole!

00:41:03.004 --> 00:41:03.685
Jinn?

00:41:14.079 --> 00:41:16.145
You bastard. Get out of the car.

00:41:16.145 --> 00:41:17.090
Hey, asshole.

00:41:17.275 --> 00:41:18.372
I said get out of the car.

00:41:18.639 --> 00:41:20.691
Open the door, asshole!

00:41:23.484 --> 00:41:24.409
What the f*ck is wrong with you?

00:41:24.409 --> 00:41:25.907
Tell me. What the f*ck is going on with you?

00:41:25.907 --> 00:41:27.051
I don’t want to be like this anymore!

00:41:33.224 --> 00:41:34.790
I don’t want to be like this anymore.

00:41:35.283 --> 00:41:36.782
I don’t want to be like this anymore.

00:41:45.163 --> 00:41:47.317
I don’t want to be like this anymore, Jinn.

00:41:50.008 --> 00:41:52.341
I want it to stop. I don’t want to be like this.

00:41:53.820 --> 00:41:55.917
I don’t want to be like this anymore, Jinn.

00:41:57.067 --> 00:41:58.637
I don’t want to be like this anymore.

00:42:00.116 --> 00:42:01.945
I’m done. I don’t want it.

00:42:06.423 --> 00:42:07.718
It’s okay, J.

00:42:08.124 --> 00:42:09.750
I really don’t want to be like this anymore.

00:42:12.777 --> 00:42:13.691
It’s alright.

00:42:30.197 --> 00:42:33.391
So when I see you having nightmares
and waking up at night all the time,

00:42:35.774 --> 00:42:37.293
you’re actually…

00:42:49.545 --> 00:42:51.119
I know it’s hard to believe.

00:42:52.351 --> 00:42:53.598
But I’ve proved everything.

00:42:55.857 --> 00:42:56.727
Proved how?

00:42:58.884 --> 00:43:02.454
I know exactly how you take your coffee,
down to every spoon.

00:43:03.768 --> 00:43:08.247
I know you love strawberry ice cream
even though you try so hard to hide it.

00:43:10.322 --> 00:43:15.258
I knew your notebook was in
your underwear drawer because…

00:43:15.874 --> 00:43:16.871
I dreamed about it.

00:43:25.890 --> 00:43:26.929
So, that means…

00:43:28.614 --> 00:43:30.647
yesterday, you knew I was going to
get hit by that bike?

00:43:32.783 --> 00:43:36.656
Normally, the visions I see
are way in the future.

00:43:37.785 --> 00:43:39.320
It’s rare to see something this near.

00:43:46.550 --> 00:43:49.273
Is this why you seem more mature?

00:43:51.430 --> 00:43:52.719
You think so?

00:43:54.095 --> 00:43:54.815
Why?

00:43:57.218 --> 00:43:59.385
There are moments
when you’re steadier than me,

00:43:59.878 --> 00:44:01.027
calmer than me.

00:44:02.834 --> 00:44:04.590
Sometimes you just ignore me
when I try to pick a fight.

00:44:06.398 --> 00:44:08.870
If it were before, we’d be
beating each other up already.

00:44:10.000 --> 00:44:11.272
There’s no way we could’ve lived together.

00:44:14.538 --> 00:44:15.727
I didn’t realize that.

00:44:16.754 --> 00:44:17.918
How could you?

00:44:18.781 --> 00:44:22.809
You then and you now are still you.

00:44:27.697 --> 00:44:31.776
So what other visions
do you see far in the future?

00:44:40.118 --> 00:44:41.146
I see…

00:44:43.035 --> 00:44:46.967
our future, ten years from now.

00:44:49.689 --> 00:44:50.432
Our?

00:44:52.589 --> 00:44:58.197
When I said that the notebook helped me
realize my feelings, I wasn’t joking.

00:44:58.978 --> 00:45:00.743
